#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:60
msgid "How-to use vixie-cron"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:64
msgid ""
"The cron daemon consults so-called crontabs for jobs to execute. These "
"crontabs are ordinary textfiles, however you should always use the crontab "
"tool to manipulate them."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:68
msgid ""
"To have a look at your crontab execute crontab -l. If a crontab exists then "
"it's contents is listed, otherwise \"no crontab for <username>\" will be "
"displayed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:71
msgid ""
"To add or delete an entry in your crontab, use crontab -e. Which editor is "
"used can be customized, but usually it's vi or whatever is in EDITOR "
"variable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:74
msgid ""
"You add or delete entries by adding or deleting the appropriate line in the "
"crontab (every entry takes exactly one line)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:78
msgid ""
"Each line consists of six columns which are seperated by blanks. The sixth "
"(rightmost) column tells cron which command/file to execute (always use the "
"full path here), while the other five columns tell cron when to execute it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:81
msgid ""
"The columns (1 stands for the leftmost column, counting to the right) have "
"the following meaning and take the values in brackets:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:87
msgid ""
"Minute (0 - 59)  Hour (0 - 23)  Day of month (1 - 31)  Month (1 - 12)  Day "
"of the week (0 - 6, 0 representing sunday, 6 saturday)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:92
msgid ""
"In each of these five columns an asterisk (\"*\") stands for \"every\".  "
"Example: \"41 5 * * * /home/jim/backupmeup.sh\" would mean that everyday at "
"5:41 in the morning the script backmeup.sh in jim's home directory would be "
"executed (assuming, of course, that the script is executable)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:96
msgid ""
"If you want to specify a group of times, then concatenate the individual "
"values, seperated by commas (Example: \"00,15,30,45\" - in the first column "
"this would read as \"every quarter of an hour on the quarter of the hour\")."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: origin/vixie-cron.txt:99
msgid ""
"If you want to specify a range of times, you can use the minus (Example: "
"\"1-5\" in the fifth column would read as \"every workday\")."
msgstr ""

